1 filing a separate return and an additional ten dollars ($10) for the
2 spouse of a taxpayer if a separate return is made by the taxpayer
3 and if the spouse, for the calendar year in which the taxable year of
4 the taxpayer begins, had no Kentucky gross income and is not the
5 dependent of another taxpayer; or twenty dollars ($20) for married
6 persons filing a joint return, provided neither spouse is the
7 dependent of another taxpayer. The determination of marital status
8 for the purpose of this section shall be made in the manner
9 prescribed in Section 153 of the Internal Revenue Code;
10 3. a. For taxable years beginning before January 1, 2014, twenty dollars
11 ($20) credit for each dependent. No credit shall be allowed for any
12 dependent who has made a joint return with his or her spouse; and
13 b. For taxable years beginning on or after January 1, 2014, and
14 before January 1, 2018, ten dollars ($10) credit for each
15 dependent. No credit shall be allowed for any dependent who has
16 made a joint return with his or her spouse;
17 4. An additional forty dollars ($40) credit if the taxpayer has attained the
18 age of sixty-five (65) before the close of the taxable year;
19 5. An additional forty dollars ($40) credit for taxpayer's spouse if a
20 separate return is made by the taxpayer and if the taxpayer's spouse has
21 attained the age of sixty-five (65) before the close of the taxable year,
22 and, for the calendar year in which the taxable year of the taxpayer
23 begins, has no Kentucky gross income and is not the dependent of
24 another taxpayer;
25 6. An additional forty dollars ($40) credit if the taxpayer is blind at the
26 close of the taxable year;
27 7. An additional forty dollars ($40) credit for taxpayer's spouse if a
